children.name: subtotal
children.description: Raw (menu) cost of order/goods that consumer sees (pre-tax, tip, fees) Marketplace + Drive + Storefront

children.name: Gov
children.description: Gross Order Value.Sum of cash inflow that DoorDash generates that comes from consumers (end users) i.e Subtotal + Tax + Tip + Cx Fees

children.name: Total Other Revenue
children.description: Summation of revenues from Legacy and gift cards

children.name: Gross Fees
children.description: Cx Fees + Mx Fees + Other Revenue

children.name: Dasher Base Pay
children.description: Base pay our Dashers receive for fulfilling an order

children.name: Dasher Incentive Pay
children.description: Bonus pay DoorDash pays Dashers to incentive/mobilize Dashers to get on the road as fast as possible

children.name: Dasher Referrals
children.description: Incentive that DoorDash pays to new Dashers who have been referred on to the platform (i.e. the person who got referred)

children.name: Fast Pay Revenue
children.description: Revenue that DoorDash collects from Dashers for using instant deposit (i.e. withdrawing money from account instantly)

children.name: Dasher Costs
children.description: Contra revenue items associated with Dasher costs

children.name: Total Refunds
children.description: Cash refunds that DoorDash provides to consumers

children.name: Support Credits
children.description: Credit redemptions in a given period

children.name: Credit Issuance Expense
children.description: Change in Credit Issuance balance on balance sheet, not the actual cost of credits given out in a period

children.name: Total Refunds
children.description: Sum of Issued credits and refunds

children.name: Bundles Pricing Discount
children.description: Discount that DoorDash provides for bundled orders - no extra delivery fee on the additional/bundled order

children.name: Consumer Referrals
children.description: Incentive that DoorDash pays to new consumers who have been referred on to the platform (i.e. the person who got referred)

children.name: Drive Maas Advertising
children.description: Ad spend that DoorDash spends to promote Drive merchants through various advertising channels.MaaS = Marketing as a Service

children.name: FMX
children.description: First Month $X.Promotion that DoorDash offers new consumers in their first month - free or discounted delivery fees on subsequent orders after 1st order

children.name: First Delivery Discount
children.description: First Delivery Free (or any variation such as FD1 - First Delivery $1) Promotion that DoorDash offers new consumers on their first delivery - free or discounted delivery fees (FDF)

children.name: Operational Error
children.description: Marqueta undercharge expense that DD ultimately pays for. This is in the case of red card usage where the in-app menu price is cheaper than the actual swiped amount in store. The delta is covered by DD instead of passed back to the consumer.Additionally, there are also situations where our app menu prices are overstated and we charge the customer more. Thus, we end up refunding the difference to the customer. This is an offset instead of a true cost to the P&L because gross fees will have the benefit of the overcharge.

children.name: Other Promotions
children.description: Other consumer promotions that do not fall into lines above

children.name: Payments To Customers
children.description: Miscellaneous payments that DoorDash makes to merchants, such as sales guarantees, royalties, contractual discounts, etc.

children.name: Promotions New Customers
children.description: Promotions/discounts for new consumes (that do not involve delivery fees)

children.name: Shipping Costs
children.description: shipping_costs

children.name: Total Discounts
children.description: Contra revenue items associated with discounts and promotions

children.name: RC&P
children.description: refund_credits_and_promotions

children.name: Net Revenue
children.description: Gross Fees - Dasher Costs - R&C - Discounts - Chase

children.name: Auto Insurance Expense
children.description: Auto insurance premium that DoorDash pays to 3rd parties to insure Dashers while they are active;Also includes auto loss reserve expense

children.name: Cancellations
children.description: Cost that DoorDash pays to the merchant for a canceled order

children.name: Cost Of Gift Cards
children.description: Cost that DoorDash pays to third party vendor as a fee for servicing our gift cards

children.name: Cost Of Lease And Equipment
children.description: Lease expense for DashMart facilities and ghost kitchens

children.name: Courier Pay
children.description: Wages that DoorDash pays to W2 couriers as part of DashForce (for 15 minute deliveries)

children.name: Dasher Pay On Cancellations
children.description: Pay that Dashers receive on canceled orders. Note that this cost is separate from the Dasher Base and Dasher Other lines in the Dasher Costs bucket, which only apply to completed/fulfilled orders.

children.name: Dasher Pay On Redeliveries
children.description: Pay that Dashers receieve on redelivered orders. Note that this cost is separate from the Dasher Base and Dasher Other lines in the Dasher Costs bucket, which only apply to the original order.

children.name: Drive Maas Management Fees
children.description: Management fee that DoorDash pays for Drive MaaS Advertising

children.name: Fast Pay Fees
children.description: Payment processing fees that DoorDash pays in order to offer Dashers the Fast Pay service (instant deposit)

children.name: Inventory Costs
children.description: Cost of inventory that is sold through DashMart

children.name: Middleware Provider Fee
children.description: Integration fees that DoorDash pays to middleware providers

children.name: Order Fullfillment Labor
children.description: Labor costs for the labor force that DoorDash employs for DashMart and ghost kitchens.

children.name: Order Placement
children.description: Cost that DoorDash pays to agents/vendors/automated services that place orders to non-partner merchants

children.name: Payment Processing Fees
children.description: Payment processing fees that DoorDash pays

children.name: Redeliveries
children.description: Cost (subtotal + tax) of redelivering an order to consumer

children.name: Release Of  Mx Unpaid Liability
children.description: Release of cash balance (liability) on balance sheet that is set aside to pay merchants that claim to be unpaid

children.name: Royalties
children.description: Royalty revenue that DoorDash receives from Marqeta (Red Card provider) as a revenue share for running transaction volume through their platform (% of GOV)

children.name: Umbrella Insurance
children.description: Insurance premium that DoorDash pays for umbrella insurance - additional insurance that provides protection beyond existing limits and coverages of other policies

children.name: Total Cost of Sales
children.description: COGS

children.name: Support
children.description: Cost of support agents and technology costs (e.g. Salesforce)

children.name: Variable Profit
children.description: Revenue - Cost of Sales - Redeliveries - Support

children.name: DES Facilities
children.description: Legacy

children.name: Dasher Onboarding
children.description: Costs for services associated with onboarding new Dashers (primarily background checks)

children.name: Dasher PPE
children.description: Costs of personal protective equipment (PPE) that DoorDash provides Dashers as a response to COVID (e.g. masks, wipes, sanitizer, gloves, etc.)

children.name: Dasher Subsidies
children.description: Subsidies that DoorDash pays Dashers (i.e. sick pay)

children.name: Internet Servers
children.description: Platform costs for hosting the website/app (e.g. AWS)

children.name: Merchant Menu Cost
children.description: Cost of getting/updating a merchants menu onto our app/platform
